<TITLE> Padma bridge pre-construction starts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Munshiganj, May 24 (bdnews24.com)Communications minister Abul Hossain on Sunday said pre-construction of Padma bridge has started by testing soil in Munshiganj. "Half the budget for the bridge is ready. Pre-construction of the Padma bridge has been kicked off," the minister told reporters. "No surcharge will be taken for Padma bridge. This bridge will be made with donors' money. The deficit of 600 crore taka has already been covered." "Land acquisitions and other works are almost in the final stage." The minister, accompanied by ambassadors of Japan and Kuwait, officials of communication ministry, World Bank, Asian Development Bank, country director of JICA, visited some parts of the project area in Munshiganj, Madaripur and Shariatpur. They talked to local people, local administration, and consultants. Hossain visited acquisitioned land areas of Bakhrerkandi in Shibchar in Madaripur district. He told the land owners that the government would pay the compensation and price of the land in time. bdne
